  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Process R&D Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Roles and Responsibilities:</strong></p><p>Build and iterate <strong>bench‑top demonstration units</strong> that integrate multiple unit operations. You’ll prototype mechanical designs, implement controls & in‑line measurements, close <strong>mass/energy balances</strong>, and generate P&IDs and vendor packages.</p><p><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></p><ul><li>Lead experimental process design; integrate unit operations into a bench‑top demo.</li><li>Prototype unit operations and implement design iterations (strong hands‑on mechanical skills).</li><li>Optimise operations & controls; implement practical reliability improvements.</li><li>Establish/test measurement strategies (in‑line sensors, data historians); close <strong>M&E balances</strong>.</li><li>Perform equipment sizing (tanks, mixers, reactors, separators/columns, pumps, valves).</li><li>Develop equipment/instrument lists, specs, and supplier options; coordinate with SMEs on materials   selection.</li><li>Prepare <strong>P&IDs</strong>, detailed specs, draft cost estimates, and project schedules.</li><li>Write operating procedures (start‑up, shutdown, normal & emergency), and sampling plans.</li></ul><p><strong>Qualifications</strong></p><ul><li>Degree in Chemical/Mechanical Engineering (or related).</li><li>3–7+ years in process development, prototyping, and pilot/demonstrator build.</li><li>Proficient with CAD, instrumentation basics, and technical documentation.</li></ul>",
